        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 6 at 2:52PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 251 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Oak Grove, or near Howell, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Cohoctah and Oak Grove around 255 PM EDT.
Fenton and Linden around 305 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Argentine, Tyrone
Township, and Deerfield Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
